com.tailf.ncs.alarmman.common

Class AlarmId

  • Object
    • com.tailf.ncs.alarmman.common.AlarmId

  • public class AlarmId
extends Object
    This class represents the unique identity of an NCS alarm. An NCS alarm is uniquely identified by the following properties:
    • managed-device
    • alarm-type
    • managed-object
    • specificProblem

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Object o)

        A unique Alarm instance is the combination of ManagedDevice, ManagedObject, (alarmtype) ConfIdentityRef and (specific problem)ConfBuf

        Compares the specified object with this AlarmId for equality. Returns true if and only if the specified object is also a AlarmId This implementation first checks if the specified object is this AlarmId. If so, it returns true; if not, it checks if the specified object is a AlarmId. If not, it returns false; if so, compares ManagedDevice,ManagedObject,AlarmType and specific problem If any comparison returns false, this method returns false.
